Mongolia Energy Corp.  agreed to issue
HK$466.8 million of 3.5 percent convertible notes due 2013 to
funds run by  Och-Ziff Capital Management Group LLC , the company
said in a Hong Kong stock exchange filing.  The company also granted an option for the subcribers to
buy a further HK$311.2 million of the notes within six months,
according to todayâ€™s statement. Mongolia Energy said it plans to
use the money to develop its Khushuut coking coal project in
